headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE.; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. FROM THE CAPITAL. No Fishery Treaty--Increase of the Army--The Gannison Massacre.

docs.lead_paragraph: You may rely positivety on the statement that no Fishery treaty has yet been agreed upon with the British Minister, not withstanding the reiteration of the story, nor is there any more probability of getting one now than months ago. The British Minister demands impossibilities.

headline.main: A Column for Young Men on Small Wages.

docs.lead_paragraph: If a man has steady business and is receiving wages, it is a duty to lay up something out of it. When one is learning a trade it is different, but after he has got his trade or profession-has fairly started, and has plenty of work, it is a great shame if he does not "get ahead" in his money affairs.

docs.lead_paragraph: DEATH OF ANSON G. PHELPS, ESQ.--We regret to announce the death of ANSON G. PHELPS, Esq., an old anti highly respected citizen. Mr. PHELPS died yesterday morning at his residence in this City, at the advanced age of 73 years.
